                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51637/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-17T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Department informed by Federal Reserve Board that Federal Reserve Bank of
                    Boston has expressed a desire to open an agency in Habana, and if agency is
                    established First National Bank of Boston will open a branch office in Habana.
                    In view of present crisis Department desires expression of your opinion on
                    matter before informing Federal Reserve Board that there is no objection to
                    establishment of proposed agency by Bank.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
